The mayor of a cash-strapped Eastern Cape municipality has been accused of hiring a municipal manager against his council’s resolution. The Daily Dispatch can reveal today that the Cradock-based Inxuba Yethemba municipality’s new municipal manager, Xolela Msweli, was hired after mayor Ray Shweni signed off on an appointment letter in February and subsequently wrote to cooperative governance and traditional affairs (Cogta) MEC Fikile Xasa asking him to concur with it. For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.